    "created_at": "2015-06-11T19:37:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-11T19:37:22Z",
    "body": "I actually think it _is_ the best approach, because it doesn't require integrating with Chromium in any way\n\n> Inhibiting the screensaver is a platform-specific operation\n\nI don't know how this would be any different in a node module vs in Electron. You'll have #ifdefs either way\n\n> On the other hand, the functionality is embedded somewhere in libchromium\n\nAs far as I can see, this isn't true - the only place I see where you can inhibit the screensaver is in the Pepper Flash host, and it's a one-off Windows only thing. The cross-platform support for screensavers in Chromium seems to only be to query whether it's running or not. \n"
  },
